QID224","LeftOperand":"q:\/\/QID224\/SelectableChoice\/10","Type":"Expression","LogicType":"Question","Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">Or<\/span> <span class=\"QuestionDesc\">What is the highest level of education you have completed?<\/span> <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">Doctorate or equivalent (e.g., PhD, JD, MD, DDS)<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Selected<\/span> ","Conjuction":"Or"},"Type":"If"},"Type":"BooleanExpression","inPage":true}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6imZX3bWIpllbIq","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID227","SecondaryAttribute":"Below there is a drop-down box containing different domains that exist within a typical company....","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Below there is a drop-down box containing different domains that exist within a typical company.\n<br><br>&nbsp;Select the domain that is the closest match to your job role.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q2.11","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"DL","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Below there is a drop-down box containing different domains that exist within a typical company....","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Manual or physical work: warehouse or logistics"},"2":{"Display":"Manual or physical work: manufacture, maintenance or repair"},"3":{"Display":"Computer or digital work: numerical, data or programming"},"4":{"Display":"Computer or digital work: administrative, organisation or planning"},"5":{"Display":"Computer or office work: customer service, marketing or HR"},"6":{"Display":"Face to face work: hospitality, sales or client care"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3","4","5","6"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":7,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID227"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6imZX3bWIpllbIq","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID35","SecondaryAttribute":"DEBRIEFING Thank you for participating in this study. We will now explain a bit more about the ba...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt\">DEBRIEFING<\/span><\/b><\/span><\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"line-height:11.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Thank you for participating in this study. We will now explain a bit more about the background and aims of the study. <\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"line-height:11.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">This questionnaire is part of a broader project aiming to develop robust assessment methods that can be used to evaluate the cognitive capabilities of both humans and Artificial Intelligence (AI) systems. This questionnaire aims to identify core cognitive capabilities that are relevant to a range of jobs and common workplace tasks. We are interested in how AI can be used to augment workplace productivity, but we are also keen to identify and safeguard uniquely human capabilities.<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"line-height:11.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you would like to learn more about the topic of the research, you might find the following literature of interest:<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><br \/>\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"line-height:11.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Cheke, L.,&nbsp;M. Halina&nbsp;and&nbsp;M. Crosby (2021), &quot;Common sense skills: Artificial intelligence and the workplace&quot;, in&nbsp;<i>AI and the Future of Skills, Volume 1:&nbsp;Capabilities and Assessments<\/i>, OECD Publishing, Paris,&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1787\/5fe70a0c-en\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1787\/5fe70a0c-en<\/a>.<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"line-height:11.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Hern&aacute;ndez-Orallo, J. (2021), &quot;Identifying artificial intelligence capabilities: What and how to test&quot;, in&nbsp;<i>AI and the Future of Skills, Volume 1:&nbsp;Capabilities and Assessments<\/i>, OECD Publishing, Paris,&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1787\/85aeb432-en\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1787\/85aeb432-en<\/a>.<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"line-height:11.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you have any questions about the study, feel free to contact the researchers: Lorenzo Pacchiardi, at<b>&nbsp;lp666<\/b>@cam.ac.uk, or Jonathan Prunty, at <b>jep84<\/b>@cam.ac.uk<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"line-height:11.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Thank you once again for your help with this research. <\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><br \/>\n&nbsp;","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q6.5","QuestionID":"QID35","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"DEBRIEFING Thank you for participating in this study. We will now explain a bit more about the ba...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":7,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6imZX3bWIpllbIq","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID46","SecondaryAttribute":"Below is the list of 5 tasks you selected as being important for your job. Drag and drop the task...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Below is the list of 5 tasks you selected as being important for your job. <br><br>Drag and drop the tasks to rank them in order of importance, with the most important task at the top (1), and least important at the bottom (5).<br><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"RO","Selector":"DND","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Below is the list of 5 tasks you selected as being important for your job. Drag and drop the task...","Choices":[],"ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":1,"NextAnswerId":1,"DynamicChoices":{"DynamicType":"ChoiceGroup","Locator":"q:\/\/QID157\/ChoiceGroup\/SelectedChoicesTextEntry","Type":"Dynamic"},"DynamicChoicesData":[],"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Below is the list of 5 tasks you selected as being important for your job. <br><br>Drag and drop the tasks to rank them in order of importance, with the most important task at the top (1), and least important at the bottom (5).<br><br>","DataExportTag":"Q3.2","QuestionID":"QID46","RecodeValues":{"x1":"1","x2":"2","x3":"3","x4":"4","x5":"5","x6":"6","x7":"7","x8":"8","x9":"9","x10":"10","x11":"11","x12":"12","x13":"13","x47":"14","x48":"15","x52":"16","x53":"17","x54":"18","x55":"19","x56":"20","x57":"21"}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6imZX3bWIpllbIq","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID47","SecondaryAttribute":"The 5 important job tasks that you selected are listed below. Use the boxes to state approximatel...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The 5 important job tasks that you selected are listed below.<br><br>Use the boxes to state approximately how many hours per week you dedicate to each task. <br><br>The hours for each task might overlap, so the total may not exactly match the number of hours you work per week.<br><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"CS","Selector":"VRTL","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":1,"CSSliderMax":100},"QuestionDescription":"The 5 important job tasks that you selected are listed below. Use the boxes to state approximatel...","Choices":[],"DynamicChoices":{"DynamicType":"ChoiceGroup","Locator":"q:\/\/QID157\/ChoiceGroup\/SelectedChoicesTextEntry","Type":"Dynamic"},"DynamicChoicesData":[],"ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"EnforceRange":"ON","Type":"None","ChoiceTotal":"100"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":1,"NextAnswerId":1,"Labels":[],"ClarifyingSymbolType":"None","QuestionText_Unsafe":"The 5 important job tasks that you selected are listed below.<br><br>Use the boxes to state approximately how many hours per week you dedicate to each task. <br><br>The time you spend on each task may be overlapping, so the 'total' number of hours may not precisely match the total number of hours that you work per week.<br><br><br>","DataExportTag":"Q3.3","QuestionID":"QID47","RecodeValues":{"x1":"1","x2":"2","x3":"3","x4":"4","x5":"5","x6":"6","x7":"7","x8":"8","x9":"9","x10":"10","x11":"11","x12":"12","x13":"13","x47":"14","x48":"15","x52":"16","x53":"17","x54":"18","x55":"19","x56":"20","x57":"21"}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6imZX3bWIpllbIq","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID49","SecondaryAttribute":"The 5 important job tasks are listed below once again. Imagine performing each task in the contex...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The 5 important job tasks are listed below once again.<br><br>Imagine performing each task in the context of your job. Use the sliders to rate how \"social\" you believe each task to be within your job specifically.<br><br>Social tasks involve dealing with people. For example, serving customers, discussing ideas with colleagues, and caring for patients are all highly social tasks.<br><br>Rate each task from not at all social (0) to completely social (100), using the sliders below.<br><br><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":5,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","StarCount":5,"StarType":"discrete","ShowValue":true,"CustomStart":false,"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"The 5 important job tasks are listed below once again. Imagine performing each task in the contex...","Choices":[],"DynamicChoices":{"DynamicType":"ChoiceGroup","Locator":"q:\/\/QID157\/ChoiceGroup\/SelectedChoicesTextEntry","Type":"Dynamic"},"DynamicChoicesData":[],"ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":1,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"How social is this task?"}},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The 5 important job tasks are listed below once again.<br><br>Similar to before, imagine performing each task in the context of your job. Use the sliders to rate how \"social\" you believe each task to be within your job specifically.<br><br>Social tasks involve dealing with people in the environment. For example, serving customers, discussing ideas with colleagues, and caring for patients are all highly social tasks.<br><br>Rate each task from not at all social (0) to completely social (100), using the sliders below.<br><br><br>","DataExportTag":"Q3.4","QuestionID":"QID49"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6imZX3bWIpllbIq","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID7","SecondaryAttribute":"What is your job title?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"What is your job title?","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q2.1","QuestionType":"TE","Selector":"SL","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"What is your job title?","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"SearchSource":{"AllowFreeResponse":"false"},"QuestionID":"QID7","QuestionText_Unsafe":"What is your job title?"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6imZX3bWIpllbIq","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID9","SecondaryAttribute":"What organisation do you work for?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"What organisation do you work for?","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q2.2","QuestionType":"TE","Selector":"SL","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"What organisation do you work for?","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"SearchSource":{"AllowFreeResponse":"false"},"QuestionID":"QID9","QuestionText_Unsafe":"What organisation do you work for?"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6imZX3bWIpllbIq","Element":"STAT","PrimaryAttribute":"Survey Statistics","SecondaryAttribute":null,"TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"MobileCompatible":true,"ID":"Survey Statistics"}}]}